pokedexEntries.red: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.
pokedexEntries.blue: A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.
pokedexEntries.gold: It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.
pokedexEntries.silver: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punching holes through thick steel.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It firmly plants its feet on the ground before shooting water from the jets on its back.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
pokedexEntries.emerald: The waterspouts that protrude from its shell are highly accurate. Their bullets of water can precisely nail tin cans from a distance of over 160 feet.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokémon's shell are used for high-speed tackles.
pokedexEntries.diamond: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.
